headline: 3 S&P 500 Stocks That Concern Us
summary: The S&P 500 is often seen as a benchmark for strong businesses, but that doesn’t mean every stock is worth owning. Some companies face significant challenges, whether it’s stagnating growth, heavy debt, or disruptive new competitors.
